# Codebase Health & Architectural Refinement Plan

This plan synthesizes the architectural assessments to ruthlessly eliminate technical debt, dead code, and SRP violations. The strategy follows a risk-mitigation path: starting with "leaf" deletions and progressing toward core structural refactoring.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan involves deleting several directories and refactoring the core synchronization engine. While Phase 1 is low-risk, later phases—specifically the Sync Engine refactor—require mandatory automated unit testing to prevent silent data loss.

